{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "name": "Grey-eared honeyeater", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "name": "Grey-eared honeyeater", "latinName": "Lichmera incana", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Grey-eared honeyeater（Lichmera incana）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Grey-eared honeyeater。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 641.03, "y": 294.28, "z": 672.6}, {"id": "bird-grey-eared-honeyeater-8a7ab8ff", "name": "Grey-eared honeyeater", "englishName": "Grey-eared honeyeater", "latinName": "Lichmera incana", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The grey-eared honeyeater (Lichmera incana), also known as the dark-brown honeyeater, is a passerine bird of the honeyeater family which is found in Vanuatu and New Caledonia in the south-west Pacific. It is sometimes known as the silver-eared honeyeater, but this name is also used for the silver-eared honeyeater (Lichmera alboauricularis) of New Guinea. Description The grey-eared honeyeater is 13 to 17 cm long with the males being larger than the females. The plumage is mainly dull green-brown above and grey with an olive tint below. The cheeks are silvery-grey, and the crown is dark grey. The black bill is long and slightly downcurved; the legs and feet are blue-grey. Juveniles are paler than the adults without the silvery cheeks. They are noisy birds which begin calling before dawn. They have a harsh tchoo-tchoo-tchoo call and a warbling song. Distribution and habitat It is a common bird across most of its range and occurs in the lowlands and low hills in a variety of habitats, including forest, scrub, mangroves, and gardens. There are five subspecies; the nominate subspecies L. i. incana is found on Grande Terre, the main island of New Caledonia. L. i. poliotis and L. i. mareensis are found on the Loyalty Islands to the north-east of New Caledonia. L. i. flavotincta and L. i. griseoviridis occur in Vanuatu. Behaviour Feeding Grey-eared honeyeaters feed from the shrub layer up to the canopy, moving from branch to branch in search of flowers from which they take nectar and pollen. They also feed on insects and spiders, searching among leaves or making short flights into the air to catch them. They will sometimes hover in front of flowers or spider webs looking for food. Reproduction The breeding season usually lasts from October to February. The nest is made mainly of grass and plant fibres, held together by spider webs. It is built in the fork of a branch in a tree or bush. Two eggs are laid; these are white with a few reddish spots and are incubated for 14 days. The young birds are fed on insects and spiders and leave the nest after 12 days. References Bregulla, Heinrich L. (1992) Birds of Vanuatu, Anthony Nelson, Oswestry, England. Doughty, Chris; Nicolas Day, Nicolas & Andrew Plant (1999) Birds of the Solomons, Vanuatu & New Caledonia, Christopher Helm, London. External links Photo of a dark-brown honeyeater - Australasian Bird Image Database", "shortSummary": "The grey-eared honeyeater (Lichmera incana), also known as the dark-brown honeyeater, is a passerine bird of the honeyeater family which is…", "locations": ["约翰·莱瑟姆 (鸟类学家)", "瓦努阿图", "新喀里多尼亞"], "lat": -17.0, "lng": 168.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Grey-eared_Honeyeater_0A2A6056.jpg/960px-Grey-eared_Honeyeater_0A2A6056.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-lichmera", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-lichmera", "species": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana"}, "expandable": true, "x": 641.03, "y": 294.28, "z": 675.93}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-lichmera", "name": "Lichmera", "latinName": "Lichmera", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Lichmera（Lichmera）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联10种鸟类，如Scaly-crowned honeyeater、Olive honeyeater、Brown honeyeater等10种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 10, "x": 665.85, "y": 123.66, "z": -90.4}], "links": [{"key": "bird-grey-eared-honeyeater-8a7ab8ff__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "source": "bird-grey-eared-honeyeater-8a7ab8ff", "target": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-lichmera", "source": "taxonomy-species-lichmera-incana", "target": "taxonomy-genus-lichmera", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Grey-eared honeyeater 属于属 Lichmera。"}]}
